  "id": "naive_trust",
  "title": "The Blindness of Faith",
  "description": "You take people at their word, believe their stories, trust their intentions—often to your detriment.",
  "content": "You want to see the best in people, so you do—even when evidence suggests otherwise. When someone tells you a story, you don't think to question it. When they make promises, you assume they'll keep them. When they show you who they are, you explain it away. You've been burned before, but you keep touching the fire, convinced that this time will be different. Cynicism feels like giving up on humanity, so you choose belief. But belief keeps costing you.",
