      "id": "learn_skepticism",
      "text": "Start questioning what you're told",
      "description": "Trust, but verify.",
      "resultText": "You begin the uncomfortable work of developing healthy skepticism. When someone tells you something, you pause before accepting it. When they make promises, you note them and wait to see if they deliver. When their actions contradict their words, you notice. It feels wrong at first, like becoming someone you don't want to be. But you also stop getting hurt as often. The naivety is lifting, revealing a more complex but more accurate view of the world.",
